OL,6,FMeanwhile, The Times reported on
OL,7,FSunday evening that a group of 36 new
OL,8,FMPs would be rowing in behind the
OL,9,FGovernment and had written a letter to
OL,10,Fthe Work and Pensions Secretary Liz
OL,11,FKendall backing reforms to the system.
OL,13,FMinisters have made clear in recent
OL,14,Fweeks that there will be an overhaul
OL,15,Fgiven the "unsustainable rise in
OL,16,Fwelfare spending".
OL,18,FMs Kendall has already told Cabinet
OL,19,Fcolleagues that the current system is
OL,20,F"holding back the economy" and "bad
OL,21,Ffor people's wellbeing and health".
